modules.description: This module implements a monadic interface for handling HTTP requests and responses using Cohttp, providing functions to execute GET, POST, PUT, and DELETE requests with custom headers and URLs. It works with strings for request bodies and responses, and uses a custom `io` monad to sequence operations and handle errors via a `fail` function. Concrete use cases include interacting with RESTful APIs, sending authenticated requests with headers, and processing server responses as strings.
